                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Have you got a link?\n\nQuite possibly by the \"modern\" keyword they might mean since native modules came about? The key tech is "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/github.com\/guybedford\/es-module-shims"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " which is transitively rewriting all the native statement \"import\" statements to the libraries internal \"importShim\" on the fly, with that in place you have total control over dependency resolution\n\nI fixed the resize thing. Thanks for testing it on Librewolf!"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
