    {
        "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1771581629.118839",
        "client_msg_id": "ab3a810f-ee82-4ffd-b0b8-2c570577f411",
        "text": "Thanks <@U02E4DAQGSZ>, resizing works fine now!\n\nAll the TiddlyWiki discussions are in TiddlyWikis, so it's hard to give direct links. The issues are not about JavaScript (TW uses nothing else but JS scripts embedded in HTML), but with browser security features and restrictions on local file system access.\n\nNow that I think of it, what they want to do is save an edited file in-place, much like a document in a native app. What Lopecode offers is downloading a copy of the current state, so it's up to the user to manage different versions of the file. Maybe there is no more to it.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "e169f54bbaf8",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2021-03-12\/1859691333940_e169f54bbaf8b9b36b12_72.png",
            "first_name": "Konrad",
            "real_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
            "display_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "konrad.hinsen",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1771513720.620429",
        "parent_user_id": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "+owpw",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Thanks "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U02E4DAQGSZ"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", resizing works fine now!\n\nAll the TiddlyWiki discussions are in TiddlyWikis, so it's hard to give direct links. The issues are not about JavaScript (TW uses nothing else but JS scripts embedded in HTML), but with browser security features and restrictions on local file system access.\n\nNow that I think of it, what they want to do is save an edited file in-place, much like a document in a native app. What Lopecode offers is downloading a copy of the current state, so it's up to the user to manage different versions of the file. Maybe there is no more to it."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
